2 Kumato
660 g Chicken Breast
1 packet Italian Truffle Mayonnaise
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
2 Potato
1 packet Parmesan Cheese
1 packet Panko Breadcrumbs
1 sachet Lemon Pepper Seasoning
1 Garlic
1 drizzle olive oil
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar

Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into bite-sized chunks.
Place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

Meanwhile, halve kumato.
Finely chop garlic.
In a small bowl, combine garlic, panko breadcrumbs, Parmesan cheese, a pinch of salt and a good drizzle of olive oil.

While kumato is roasting, place your hand flat on top of chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.
In a large bowl, combine lemon pepper seasoning, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt. Add chicken steaks, turning to coat.
In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
Cook chicken steaks until cooked through, 3-6 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink inside.

Place tomato on a second lined oven tray. Spoon Parmesan garlic crumb over tomatoes and drizzle with olive oil.
Roast until tomatoes are just blistered and crumb is golden, 10-15 minutes.

In a second medium bowl, combine mixed salad, a drizzle of balsamic vinegar and olive oil. Season.

Divide potato chunks, chicken, salad and roasted Parmesan crumb kumato between plates.
Serve with Italian truffle mayonnaise. Enjoy!